1. OSI Model:
There are 7 layers:
Application, Presentation, Session, Transport, Network, Data Link, Physical.
Example protocols:
Application - HTTP
Presentation - SSL
Session - NetBIOS
Transport - TCP
Network - IP
Data Link - Ethernet
Physical - Cables
TCP works at Transport layer.

2. IP Addressing:
Public IP is used on internet.
Private IP is used inside local network.
Private IP ranges:
Class A: 10.0.0.0 - 10.255.255.255
Class B: 172.16.0.0 - 172.31.255.255
Class C: 192.168.0.0 - 192.168.255.255
192.168.1.100 is private IP.

3. Protocols:
22 - SSH
80 - HTTP
443 - HTTPS
3306 - MySQL
TCP is connection-based, UDP is faster but no guarantee.
NAT converts private IP to public IP to access internet.





